text:

Leonard Street, west side, at and north of Ten Eyck Street, showing St. Mary of the Immaculate Conception (R.C.) Church and School.

folder: Leonard Street & Ten Eyck Street, Brooklyn, NY
original_title: Brooklyn: Leonard Street - Ten Eyck Street
text:
(1)
Leonard Street, east side, south from Ten Eyck Street, showing the cleared area, formerly occupied by tenements, where the Williamsburg Houses--a low rent governmental housing center, will be erected. In the background is the steeple of the Most Holy Trinity Roman Catholic Church, on Montrose Avenue.

P. L. Sperr

(2), (3)
Across the same area, in a more easterly direction, showing a new school under construction.

P. L. Sperr

View 2: August 10, 1936
View 3: October 27, 1936
